[size=4][b]What[/b][/size]

[size=3]Skips the "Are you sure?" confirmation dialog when you pick a body part to remove at the autopsy table. One click and it's done.[/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][b]Removes the confirmation prompt entirely[/b] — your click goes straight through. There's no undo once a part is selected, so be deliberate.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]No unlock required[/b] — applies from the moment you first use the autopsy table.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Other mods of mine you might like[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/57]Queue Everything[/url] — per-workbench auto-craft supports the morgue, autopsy table, and packing table.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/89]Grave Changes Redux[/url] — lifts the grave-quality cap so high-quality body parts count fully.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/62]Where's Ma' Storage[/url] — shared inventory across every workstation; packing tables see every ingredient.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Configuration[/b][/size]

[size=3]If you installed the required [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack[/url] and this mod is configurable, press F1 in-game to open the config interface.[/size]

[size=4][b]Requirements[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79][size=3]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack at Graveyard Keeper Nexus - Mods and community (nexusmods.com)[/size][/url]
[/list]
[size=4][b]Installation[/b][/size]

[size=3]Installation using Vortex is the recommended installation method. If you wish to install manually, extract the contents of the mod archive into:

[code]...&#92;steamapps&#92;common&#92;Graveyard Keeper&#92;BepInEx[/code][/size]

